# Intern 2: Error Handling

- Every async fetch path must handle failures with `try`/`catch` or an explicit `.catch()`.
- Store user-facing failures in React error state instead of letting the UI crash.
- Show the `Connection Failed` warning card when the simulated network request fails.
- Clear stale errors before a new request starts.
- Do not swallow errors silently; make the failure visible to users or tests.
